If this is a bigger project and you have more control over the network infrastructure, it might also be a good idea to not do this in Java, but just use a separate *proxy server* in front of the Servlet container. You can control what should be cached by the usual [`Cache-Control`][1] HTTP headers (which you can set using a filter if the servlet does not already do it).


